+# RAGAS Evaluation Guide
+
+## Quick Start
+
+Run comprehensive evaluation:
+```bash
+uv run python ragblog/run.py
+```
+
+This will:
+1. Process your query about Helena/Alejandra
+2. Evaluate 6 standard test questions
+3. Generate RAGAS metrics and actionable insights
+4. Save results to `data/output.md`
+
+## Understanding RAGAS Scores
+
+### Primary Metrics
+- **Faithfulness (0-1)**: Answer grounded in context (no hallucinations)
+- **Answer Relevancy (0-1)**: Answer addresses the question
+- **Context Precision (0-1)**: Retrieved docs are relevant
+- **Context Recall (0-1)**: All relevant info retrieved
+- **Answer Correctness (0-1)**: Factual accuracy
+- **Answer Similarity (0-1)**: Semantic similarity to ground truth
+
+### Score Interpretation
+- **0.8+**: Excellent performance
+- **0.6-0.8**: Good, minor issues
+- **0.4-0.6**: Needs improvement
+- **<0.4**: Critical problems
+
+## Component Bottleneck Analysis
+
+The system automatically identifies the weakest component:
+
+### Common Bottlenecks & Fixes
+
+#### 🔍 **Retrieval Issues**
+- **Low Context Precision**: Too many irrelevant docs
+  - Solution: Enable reranking (`use_reranker: true`)
+- **Low Context Recall**: Missing relevant information
+  - Solution: Try hybrid retrieval (`use_hybrid: true`)
+
+#### ✂️ **Chunking Issues**
+- **Low Answer Relevancy**: Poor semantic alignment
+  - Solution: Switch to semantic chunking (`chunking_strategy: "semantic"`)
+
+#### 🤖 **Generation Issues**
+- **Low Faithfulness**: Hallucinations detected
+  - Solution: Better prompting or stronger LLM (`llm: "llama3.1:70b"`)
+
+## Configuration Examples
+
+### High-Performance Setup
+```yaml
+chunking_strategy: "semantic"
+use_reranker: true
+use_hybrid: true
+query_transform: "multi_query"
+embeddings: "sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2"
+llm: "llama3.1:70b"
+```
+
+### Balanced Setup
+```yaml
+chunking_strategy: "fixed"
+use_reranker: false
+use_hybrid: false
+query_transform: "none"
+embeddings: "sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2"
+llm: "llama3.1:8b"
+```
+
+## Custom Evaluation
+
+```python
+from ragblog.ragas_evaluator import RagasEvaluator
+
+evaluator = RagasEvaluator(judge_model="llama3.1:70b")
+results = evaluator.evaluate_dataset(questions, answers, contexts)
+print(results['insights']['recommendations'])
+```
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+### RAGAS Fails to Load
+```bash
+uv sync  # Install dependencies
+```
+
+### Low Scores Across All Metrics
+- Check if vector store is populated
+- Verify embedding model is working
+- Ensure blog.jsonl contains actual content
+
+### Inconsistent Results
+- RAG has inherent stochasticity
+- Use `num_runs: 3+` for statistical significance
+- Different LLMs may give different results
